      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR ULTIMATE JANE (4) drew on the back row and had to work but was too good here last time out, getting home by 1.7 metres. Up to a distance where she has won before and returns to the front line so could strike again. POSTER PERFECT (2) was close-up at her latest appearance at Shepparton, coming from a wider barrier to be beaten just 1.4 metres into fourth. Race fit fourth up and won over this distance the only time she raced here. Should get her chance from this favourable starting position. SWEET LOUANNE (1) resumes after eight months but showed some good form last time in, winning three back at Bendigo. Gets the ace draw for her return and will be ready to go after two trials. LETTUCE GO MIKI (7) draws wider but showed pleasing improvement last time out when third at Bathurst. Peaking now and won his lone try at this circuit and distance.",
